The paper focuses on the evaluation of the response to tactile enhanced multimedia content using human brain signals. This involves the use of EEG data and machine learning algorithms for emotion classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves the use of multimedia technology, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for emotion classification suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical analysis and classification algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
